  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.virtualization/documentation/Virtualization/VZVirtualMachineConfiguration",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to create a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.virtualization/documentation/Virtualization/VZMacPlatformConfiguration",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " that represents a specific macOS platform configuration (",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.virtualization/documentation/Virtualization/VZMacHardwareModel",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", number of virtual CPUs, RAM, devices, and so on) that you want to run on your Apple silicon Mac.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The Virtualization framework provides everything you need to macOS on a VM using macOS installation images you download from Apple. Use the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.virtualization/documentation/Virtualization/VZMacOSRestoreImage/latestSupported",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method of ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.virtualization/documentation/Virtualization/VZMacOSRestoreImage",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to obtain the URL for the installation media used to install the latest version of macOS. Alternatively, if youâ€™ve already downloaded a macOS release, you can construct a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "VZMacOSRestoreImage",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object using that file. The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "mostFeaturefulSupportedConfiguration",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " property of a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "VZMacOSRestoreImage",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " object specifies the requirements and recommendations that you use to configure a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.virtualization/documentation/Virtualization/VZVirtualMachineDelegate",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to complete this installation. After creating a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "VZVirtualMachine",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ", use ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.virtualization/documentation/Virtualization/VZMacOSInstaller",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to install macOS on that virtual machine. You then use this configuration to create a bootable image that, along with a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.virtualization/documentation/Virtualization/VZMacOSBootLoader",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", runs in a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.virtualization/documentation/Virtualization/VZVirtualMachine",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " that you can control.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For more information on running macOS as a guest, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Creating and Running a macOS Virtual Machine",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
